      "content": "Wait, so it's 100% resolved? I was reading some forums where people were saying the patch only covers the surface-level exploit but the underlying memory corruption issue is still there. Can you double check the technical specifics? I don't want to tell the board \"we're good\" if we're actually still wide open to a bypass. Is the core flaw actually gone?",
